  "body": "In the database layout pre THIN HISTORY, there is a convention that is there is a record in the history bucket (hAT or hST) with an empty value, it means that the record has gone from being empty to non-empty at the corresponding block number (timestamp).\r\nThis information is used, for example, in the stateGrowth analytics (the value in the record is not used, only the \"emptyness\").\r\nWhen we migrate to THIN HISTORY, we might want to preserve this by maintaining one bit of information per timestamp in the hAT (and then hST) buckets to signal that the record went from empty to non-empty.\r\nIf we do that, then stateGrowth analytics will not need to access `ChangeSet` bucket at all.",
